                            <comment id="119376" author="pwebb" created="Thu, 10 Sep 2015 01:41:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A Spring Boot user has just hit this and provided a sample project to replicate. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/issues/3923&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/issues/3923&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we&apos;ll probably need a fix before we can release Spring Boot 1.3&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="120492" author="pwebb" created="Tue, 13 Oct 2015 06:19:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any update on a fix for this? We&apos;ll be releasing 1.3.RC1 on Thursday all being well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="120510" author="rwinch" created="Tue, 13 Oct 2015 13:40:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=pwebb&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;pwebb&quot;&gt;Phil Webb&lt;/a&gt; Unfortunately there is no update on this at the moment. I have been quite preoccupied with other things. When is the GA release expected?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="120560" author="pwebb" created="Wed, 14 Oct 2015 16:40:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ideally we&apos;d like to release around the end of October.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="120826" author="rwinch" created="Wed, 21 Oct 2015 20:52:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is now resolved. The fix was to completely remove &lt;tt&gt;ConditionalOnMissingBean&lt;/tt&gt; from Spring Security to ensure we resolve &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-3062&quot; title=&quot;WebMvcSecurityConfiguration may unnecessarily create RequestDataValueProcessor&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-3062&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-3062&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; too. Now users must define &lt;tt&gt;requestDataValueProcessor&lt;/tt&gt; in the class annotated with &lt;tt&gt;@EnableWebSecurity&lt;/tt&gt; to ensure the custom &lt;tt&gt;requestDataValueProcessor&lt;/tt&gt; is used.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="126121" author="issuemaster" created="Sat, 6 Feb 2016 06:30:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue has been migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/3264&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/3264&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
